m_q.target_metric: Count of marine beaches that had zero violations from 2002 to 2023 inclusive
filters: Violation = 'no' or 'NO' or 'No' for all records per beach across all years
sub_questions: Which marine beaches have data for all years 2002-2023?
For beaches with missing years, should they be considered safe for those years?
How to handle case variations in Violation column (yes/YES/Yes, no/NO/No)?
Are there duplicate beach names across different communities/counties that need disambiguation?

schema_conflicts: Indicator Level column has different dtypes: int64 (2002) vs float64 (2003-2023)
Violation column has inconsistent casing: lowercase (2002-2018 mostly) vs uppercase (2019-2023 mostly)

scale_issues: Indicator Level values range from 1.0 to 800.0 in samples, but actual range unknown
cross_source_conflicts: 2002 file has only 650 rows vs 12k-16k rows for other years, suggesting incomplete data for 2002
2002 file has 'Fresh' beach types while other files show only 'Marine' in samples

format_notes: All files have same column names and order
Sample Date includes timestamp but appears to always be 00:00:00
First row is header in all files
Shape information provided for each file

constraints: Each row represents one water sample test
Beach Name should uniquely identify a beach location
derived_filters: Standardize Violation values to consistent case
Group by Beach Name and check for any 'yes'/'YES'/'Yes' in Violation column across all years
Count beaches with zero violations across all years
statistical_tests: Check for duplicate Beach Names across different Community/County combinations
Test assumption: missing year data = safe for that year
output_format_requirements: Must account for beaches with partial data (treat missing years as safe per question)
